												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/rebeccachace/">Rebecca Chace</a></h6>
													Rebecca Chace is the author of two novels, a memoir, and a book for middle-grade readers. Her third novel, <em>Talking to the Wolf</em>, is forthcoming from Red Hen Press in 2026. She is also a playwright, screenwriter, and a regular contributor to <em>The New York Times</em>. Her work has appeared in <em>The Yale Review</em>, <em>LA Review of Books</em>, <em>Guernica</em>, <em>Lit Hub</em>, <em>Bookpost</em>, and many other publications. Fellowships include Civitella Ranieri, MacDowell, Yaddo, Dora Maar House, American Academy in Rome (visiting artist), Virginia Center for the Creative Arts, and others. She is a Faculty Associate at the Institute for Writing and Thinking, Bard College.																									</div>
